The paper discusses a new approach to knowledge acquisition based on social network distributions, which falls under the category of social networks and their analysis. Therefore, cs.SOC is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of algorithms and machine learning techniques to improve the selection process, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of surveys and sampling techniques, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the application of the proposed approach in the area of collaborative learning, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of online social networks, which falls under the category of social computing (cs.SI).
